    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">03</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Timeline Activity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Building the Texican Identity Timeline</h2><ul><li>Mark key dates: Mexican Texas period, Texas Revolution, Republic of Texas, and statehood.</li><li>Note when 'Texican,' 'Texian,' and 'Texan' were prevalent.</li><li>Connect terminology shifts to political events.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Creating a timeline helps visualize how Texican identity terms evolved in response to political milestones from Mexican rule to U.S. statehood. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> 1820s: 'Texican' used under Mexican rule; 1835-1836: 'Texian' during revolution; 1845 onward: 'Texan' after statehood.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Construct a timeline with at least five events showing terminology changes and explain their significance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Listing events without linking them to terminology or identity changes.</p></div></div>",
