    "num": "05",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">05</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texicans’ Role in the Texas Revolution</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Contributions and Actions Leading to Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texicans participated in protests and armed resistance against Mexican centralization.</li><li>They formed militias and supported key battles like the Siege of Bexar.</li><li>Texican leaders negotiated and debated independence strategies.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans were active agents in the revolution, engaging militarily and politically to challenge Mexican authority and advocate for local governance. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican militias joined Anglo settlers in the 1835 Siege of Bexar, a pivotal early victory against Mexican forces.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify specific Texican contributions to the Texas Revolution and their significance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking Texican participation by focusing only on Anglo settlers.</p></div></div>",
