    "num": "07",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Debate Activity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Arguing Texican Perspectives on the Revolution</h2><ul><li>Divide into groups representing different Texican viewpoints.</li><li>Use primary and secondary sources to support arguments.</li><li>Discuss how Texican motivations influenced the revolution's course.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This debate fosters critical thinking by engaging learners with contested interpretations of Texican roles and motivations. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> One group argues Texicans sought independence mainly for economic freedom; another emphasizes cultural preservation.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Present your group's argument and respond to opposing views using evidence.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring opposing evidence or relying on stereotypes.</p></div></div>",
