    "num": "12",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">12</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Reflection and Transfer</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Connecting Texican Identity to Modern Texas</h2><ul><li>Consider how historical identity terms influence modern Texan culture.</li><li>Reflect on the legacy of political and cultural blending.</li><li>Explore how contested histories shape current perspectives.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Reflecting on the historical evolution of Texican identity helps learners transfer understanding to contemporary cultural and political contexts in Texas. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Modern Texans may trace heritage to Texicans, Texians, or Anglo settlers, reflecting layered identities.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief reflection on how the evolution of Texican identity informs your understanding of Texas today.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing historical identities as irrelevant to modern culture.</p></div></div>",
