    "id": "slide41",
    "eyebrow": "Source Evaluation",
    "num": "17",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">17</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Source Evaluation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Practicing Primary Source Analysis: Land Grant Excerpt</h2><ul><li>Identify key information: date, parties, conditions</li><li>Analyze language for government priorities</li><li>Corroborate with historical context</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Analyzing a land grant excerpt helps learners practice extracting factual data and interpreting the document’s purpose and implications within Texican history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A grant dated 1827 requires settlers to build a dwelling within six months and convert to Catholicism, reflecting Mexican colonization policies.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Read the excerpt and list the obligations imposed on the settler. Discuss how these reflect Mexican government goals.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking implicit cultural or political expectations embedded in legal language.</p></div></div>",
