    "eyebrow": "Source Evaluation",
    "num": "18",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">18</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Source Evaluation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing a Texican Letter: Perspective and Bias</h2><ul><li>Identify the author’s viewpoint and purpose</li><li>Note emotional tone and subjective language</li><li>Compare with other sources for corroboration</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Evaluating a letter excerpt teaches learners to recognize subjectivity and contextualize personal narratives within broader historical evidence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter expressing frustration with Mexican officials reveals settler grievances but may exaggerate conflicts for persuasive effect.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Highlight phrases indicating bias or emotion. Discuss how this affects the letter’s reliability.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Accepting personal accounts at face value without critical scrutiny.</p></div></div>",
